Mail-in-a-Box patch: frontend - remove custom server configuration from login
=============================================================================

Companion frontend patch to 1_miab_oxi_auth_patch.patch.

On a MIAB box, oxi connects to the box's own Dovecot and Postfix instances.
The server addresses and TLS settings are fixed in /etc/oxi/config.env and
should not be overridden per-login. This patch removes the server
configuration UI from the login page and add-account modal so users only
see and submit email and password.

Without this patch, the login form still renders the server config fields
and submits imap_tls/smtp_tls in the payload by default, which the backend
(patch 1) rejects.

